1. *Uveravam* te da sam iskreno pokušao da popravim grešku. (I assure you that I sincerely tried to fix the mistake.)
2. Molim vas da me *uverite* da ste razumeli sve što sam rekao. (Please, assure me that you understood everything I said.)
3. Oni će *uveriti* javnost u sigurnost novog proizvoda. (They will convince the public of the safety of the new product.)
4. Kada sam čuo njihove argumente, *uverio* sam se da nisam bio u pravu. (When I heard their arguments, I became convinced that I was wrong.)
5. Da bismo izbegli nesporazume, potrebno je da se *uverimo* u tačnost informacija. (To avoid misunderstandings, it is necessary to verify the accuracy of the information.)
6. *Uveravanje* drugih u sopstvenu ispravnost je čest oblik samozavaravanja. (Convincing others of one's own correctness is a common form of self-deception.)
7. Njegove reči nisu me *uverile* u iskrenost njegovog obećanja. (His words didn't convince me of the sincerity of his promise.)
8. *Uveren* sam da će se naš tim uspešno nositi sa svim izazovima. (I am convinced that our team will successfully cope with all challenges.)
9. Uspeli smo da *uverimo* upravu kompanije da je naša ideja vredna investiranja. (We managed to convince the company's management that our idea is worth investing in.)
10. Sve veći broj ljudi se *uverava* u važnost zaštite životne sredine. (An increasing number of people are becoming convinced of the importance of environmental protection.)